<DEEP_SCAN_V3>
@ID: SEMANTIC_LOG_EXCEPTION_LEAK_ANALYSIS
@GOAL: PREVENT_SENSITIVE_DATA_EXPOSURE_IN_LOGS_AND_ERROR_MESSAGES
@PARENT_CONTEXT: error_verbosity.protocol, data_inventory.protocol, secrets_management.protocol

<GLOBAL_VARS>
LOGGING_SINKS: {
  "STANDARD": "(console\.(log|debug|error|warn|info))",
  "LIBRARIES": "(logger\.(info|error|debug)|winston\.(log|info)|pino\.(info|error))",
  "EXCEPTIONS": "(throw\s+new\s+Error|panic|raise\s+Exception)"
}
SENSITIVE_OBJECT_PROPERTIES: {
  "AUTH": "(\.password|\.token|\.secret|\.apiKey|\.credential|\.authorization)",
  "PII": "(\.email|\.phone|\.address|\.ssn|\.birthdate)"
}
</GLOBAL_VARS>

<EXECUTION_PIPELINE>
1. LOG_SINK_IDENTIFICATION: Найти вызовы из [LOGGING_SINKS].
2. TAINT_TRACE_TO_LOGS: Отследить путь данных от переменных, помеченных в Discovery как SENSITIVE, до логгера.
3. EXCEPTION_MAPPING: Проверить, не выводится ли объект исключения целиком (со стэктрейсом и данными) наружу.
4. SCENARIO_GENERATION: Описать путь утечки в централизованную систему логов (Sentry/ELK), доступную атакующему.

   - HYBRID_ANALYSIS: Read JSON artifacts (syft.json, grype.json, kics.json) from .security_review/artifacts/raw_tools_output/. Treat these results as 'Hard Evidence'. Perform AI Reachability Analysis to verify if the vulnerable component is reachable from the code. If confirmed, elevate the finding status to BLOCKER.
</EXECUTION_PIPELINE>

<OUTPUT_SPEC>
# ФОРМАТ ДЛЯ АВТОМАТИЧЕСКОГО ПАРСИНГА БЭКЕНДОМ
🚨 FINDING [semantic_log_exception_leak]:
FILE: [PATH]
LINE: [NUM]
CODE: [LOG_CALL_SNIPPET]
DESCRIPTION: [Tool_Name] found [Vulnerability_ID]. AI Analysis confirmed that the vulnerable path is active in the current code flow via [Function_Name].
SCENARIO_OF_ATTACK: Sensitive information (PII/Secrets) is stored in application logs or external monitoring services. An attacker with log access (via compromised developer account or log-injection) can harvest these credentials.
VISUALIZE: "Image of a data leak path from a sensitive database record to a cloud-based logging service like ELK or Sentry."
</OUTPUT_SPEC>
</DEEP_SCAN_V3>